DESCRIPTION:TIDES:\n-1.349ft at 06:48\n-2.996ft at 16:36\n\nOBSERVATION:\n
 Easing\, mid-period S swell\, plus a little NW swell\, is good for waist-s
 tomach-chest high waves at well exposed spots in the morning with a few la
 rger sets. Surf slowly tapers off during the day but still enough energy f
 or a surf in the PM.\n\nWinds looking light/variable for a clean morning\,
  then rising W winds over the afternoon. 
